rows.label: tev074101_JNK0010
rows.name: Inquire[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_SEL0011
rows.name: Ask Non'barac about the Ganglion's main base.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_JNK0020
rows.name: Discuss[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_SEL0021
rows.name: Ask Non'barac if anything is troubling her.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_SEL0031
rows.name: Ask Non'barac about the fight with the Ganglion.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_SEL1021
rows.name: Ask Non'barac about recent developments.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG0001
rows.name: Ganglion's home base seems to be in Cauldros.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG0002
rows.name:
Sifting through the memories that run through my veins,
I do have a sense that most of the weapons we made
were sent north.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG0003
rows.name:
Those weapons alone would make for quite an
impressive concentration of artillery, so watch out
for that.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG0004
rows.name:
I also suspect you'll be facing defenses far beyond
anything you've seen in this area.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG0009
rows.name:
The miranium shortage is a serious problem,
but an entirely preventable one caused by the
inefficient way you humans are exploring Mira.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG0010
rows.name:
After all, outside of major missions, the exploration
is being conducted by individual teams acting on
their own initiative, is it not?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG0011
rows.name:
Unlike us, you don't have an Ovah to regulate
your efforts.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG0012
rows.name:
Wouldn't it make more sense to expand FrontierNav
in a carefully planned fashion, moving each BLADE like
a piece on a map?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG0013
rows.name:
If you leave the planning to me, I can promise that
your efforts will be 3.68 times more efficient![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG0018
rows.name:
Several of the Orphean Technologies armaments employ
parts that I've developed.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG0019
rows.name:
Have they served you well in your fight with the
Ganglion?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG0020
rows.name:
I have made a number of friends in this city,
and take pride in having been able to offer them
higher-quality items than I did to the Ganglion.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG0021
rows.name: What do you think? Were they of use?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG0022
rows.name:
If so, I hope you will continue to use them—with my
deep appreciation—to maintain a lasting peace.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG1001
rows.name:
After what happened, I had a long conversation with
a Pathfinder.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG1002
rows.name:
He spoke of having to traverse unimaginably dangerous
areas in order to install data probes.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG1003
rows.name:
Apparently he's had to install them on sheer cliffs,
in indigen nests, and even at the heart of Ganglion
fortresses![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG1004
rows.name:
With the pace at which you've been installing them
lately, I had assumed it was a much simpler task.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev074101_MSG1005
rows.name:
You humans certainly are incredible creatures.
Please keep installing those probes and bringing me
their miranium![ST:wait ]
